    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-15T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-15T11:00:00-05:00" n="227"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d227">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.94/1136.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-15T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 15, 1939—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 15—2:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1986. The Chinese Embassy in Paris informs us that Sun Fo called on Molotov
                    yesterday and requested information regarding the Soviet-Japanese negotiations
                    which he understood were being carried on.</p>
                <p>In reply Sun Fo received assurances that there would be no change in the Soviet
                    foreign policy vis-à-vis the Far East.<note n="32" xml:id="d227fn32">See also
                        telegram No. 546 bis, September 15, midnight, from the Ambassador in the
                        Soviet Union, <ref target="#pg_70">p. 70</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
